  "sitelinks": 79,
  "birth_place": "Bagnoregio",
  "description": "Franciscan, bishop, cardinal, Doctor of the Church, Catholic saint",
  "bio": "聖文德，或譯為聖文都辣、波拿文德拉、波那文都，O.F.M.（義大利語：San Bonaventura，1221年—1274年），是中世紀義大利的神學家及哲學家。作為第七任方濟各會總會長，曾任阿爾巴諾教區領銜主教。\n文德於1482年4月14被教宗西斯都四世尊奉為聖人，並於1588年被教宗西斯都五世列為教會聖師之一。文德因其完備的品德，被尊稱為「色勒芬天使博士」(拉丁語：Doctor Seraphicus)和「方濟各會第二會祖」。\n許多署名為文德中世紀的作品（其實並非文德所寫），被以「偽文德文集」為名收集起來。",
  "bio_source": "zhwiki",
  "description_en": "Franciscan, bishop, cardinal, Doctor of the Church, Catholic saint",
  "bio_en": "Bonaventure (born Giovanni di Fidanza; 1221 – 15 July 1274) was an Italian Catholic Franciscan bishop, cardinal, scholastic theologian and philosopher.\nThe seventh Minister General of the Order of Friars Minor, he also served for a time as Bishop of Albano. He was canonised on 14 April 1482 by Pope Sixtus IV. In 1588 Pope Sixtus V declared him a Doctor of the Church named as the \"Seraphic Doctor\" (Latin: Doctor Seraphicus). His feast day is 15 July.\nMany writings from the Middle Ages once attributed to him have been subsequently re-classified under the name \"Pseudo-Bonaventure\".",
  "bio_en_source": "enwiki"
}